reviews.review: This was easily Disney's best Star Wars film. The writing was the best they've done. The directing was the best they've done. The acting was the best they've done. JJ was masterful in this movie. As someone who loved The Force Awakens and HATED The Last Jedi, I absolutely LOVED The Rose of Skywalker, we'll done.

Not only a literal but also a figurative mind wipe of the ridiculousness of Rian's "the Last Jedi". This is an actual Star Wars movie, and it is an epic conclusion to the entire Skywalker saga. J.J. Strikes Back!
Although not a perfect film, I enjoyed it very much!

This movie is bad! Nothing works in its favor, save for 'looking good'. The plot sucks, the plot-holes are all over, and the 'twists' and 'surprises' are cheap and have no impact on the movie. Worse still, the ending is Mass Effect 3 levels of bad! Don't give this movie your money, period!
A drastic improvement over the last Jedi!
The movie was a satisfying and acceptable end to Star Wars. A handful of short moments that I was not pleased with, and some unwanted pandering, but the Star Wars feel was still all around the movie
wrapped everything up nicely. well done.

The negative critics here are a joke, the same critics that greatly praised the politically driven drivel that was the Last Jedi. JJ has been tasked with the seemingly impossible - creating a satisfying end to a 9 film saga, picking up from an 8th part which left nothing to work on beyond a Monty Python routine for villains and heroes that no one really cared for. Added to that you've got an environment of YouTubers who are also slating this film having now found careers and followers in the "I hate Star Wars" brigade who are desperately trying to maintain their clickbait followers that were rightfully angry with the Last Jedi. 
So with that context what has JJ achieved? An absolute monster smash. This film is epic. It made me care again for characters that were set up in the Force Awakens, it redeemed the bad treatment of heroes past such as Luke and it reminded me of why I love Star Wars. There are so many moments where I was close to tears as JJ pulled on the nostalgia, moments where I jumped out of my seat in excitement and moments when I was just in awe at the visual spectacle. 
Sure this film has flaws but they are flaws caused by the necessary retconning of the mess that was made before by Rian Johnson. When a film is being criticised that it has too much fan service - that basically means it provides an all action Star Wars rollercoaster ride reminiscent of the original trilogy and goes without the unnecessary Kathleen Kennedy driven gender, race politics.
I've seen this film twice and am booking for the third viewing in a few more days. So sad it's over but what a way to end it. If you really love Star Wars, forget the Last Jedi, forget the flaws caused by the necessary retconning and you will love this film. JJ I salute you sir, if only you were given the reins to part 8 also.
difficult comeback after Rian Johnson's stinker, but a pretty good wrap-up all things considered.
